{"title_page": "The Fabulous Allan Carr", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Fabulous Allan Carr\n| image          = The Fabulous Allan Carr.png\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Jeffrey Schwarz]]\n| producer       = John Boccardo<br>Jeffrey Schwarz\n| writer         = \n| screenplay     = \n| story          = \n| based on       = <!-- {{Based on|title of the original work|creator of the original work|additional creator(s), if necessary}} -->\n| starring       = [[Allan Carr]]\n| narrator       = \n| music          = Michael Cudahy\n| cinematography = Jeff Byrd<br>Matt May<br>Keith Walker\n| editing        = Carl Pfirman<br>Jeffrey Schwarz\n| studio         = [[Automat Pictures]]\n| distributor    = <!-- or: | distributors = -->\n| released       = May 19, 2017\n| runtime        = 90 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''The Fabulous Allan Carr''''' is a 2017 American [[documentary film]] from filmmaker [[Jeffrey Schwarz]]. The film details the story of the flamboyant Hollywood producer [[Allan Carr]], famous for producing ''[[Grease (film)|Grease]]'', ''[[Can't Stop the Music]]'', the musical adaptation of ''[[La Cage aux Folles (musical)|La Cage aux Folles]]'', and the notorious [[61st Academy Awards|1989 Academy Awards]]. The film made its debut at the 2017 Seattle International Film Festival ([[SIFF]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siff.net/festival/fabulous-allan-carr-the|title=The Fabulous Allan Carr|website=www.siff.net}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestranger.com/movies/25117345/the-fabulous-allan-carr|title=The Fabulous Allan Carr (2017) - siff Guide - The Stranger|website=The Stranger}}</ref>\n\nFeaturing interviews and archival footage with friends and confidantes of the flamboyant producer, early reviews marked ''The Fabulous Allan Carr'' as a reverent portrait of one of Hollywood's elite,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scene-stealers.com/reviews/print-reviews/siff-2017-the-fabulous-allan-carr-movie-review/|title=\u2018The Fabulous Allan Carr\u2019 Movie Review|website=www.scene-stealers.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://thesunbreak.com/2017/05/19/siff-interview-jeffrey-schwarz-allan-carr/|title=SIFF Interview: Jeffrey Schwarz on Taking on \u2018The Fabulous Allan Carr\u2019|date=19 May 2017|publisher=}}</ref> highlighting the fact that Carr \"changed the face of pop and gay culture.\"\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://seattlegayscene.com/2017/05/siff-world-premiere-the-fabulous-allan-carr/|title=SIFF World Premiere: The Fabulous Allan Carr - Seattle Gay Scene - Your Daily Gay In Seattle|website=seattlegayscene.com}}</ref>\n\nThe film features interviews with [[Patricia Birch]], [[Maxwell Caulfield]], [[Steve Guttenberg]], [[Randy Jones (singer)|Randy Jones]], [[Randal Kleiser]], [[Sherry Lansing]], [[Lorna Luft]], [[Michael Musto]], [[Robert Osborne]], [[Brett Ratner]], [[Connie Stevens]], [[Alana Stewart]], [[Marlo Thomas]], [[Bruce Vilanch]] and more.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official|http://www.allancarrmovie.com/}}\n* {{facebook|allancarrmovie}}\n* {{imdb title|4704904}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fabulous Allan, The}}\n[[Category:Documentary films about film directors and producers]]\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American documentary films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n\n\n{{arts-documentary-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Fabulous Allan Carr\n| image          = The Fabulous Allan Carr.png\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Jeffrey Schwarz]]\n| producer       = John Boccardo<br>Jeffrey Schwarz\n| writer         = \n| screenplay     = \n| story          = \n| based on       = <!-- {{Based on|title of the original work|creator of the original work|additional creator(s), if necessary}} -->\n| starring       = [[Allan Carr]]\n| narrator       = \n| music          = Michael Cudahy\n| cinematography = Jeff Byrd<br>Matt May<br>Keith Walker\n| editing        = Carl Pfirman<br>Jeffrey Schwarz\n| studio         = [[Automat Pictures]]\n| distributor    = <!-- or: | distributors = -->\n| released       = May 19, 2017\n| runtime        = 90 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''The Fabulous Allan Carr''''' is a 2017 American [[documentary film]] from filmmaker [[Jeffrey Schwarz]]. The film details the story of the flamboyant Hollywood producer [[Allan Carr]], famous for producing ''[[Grease (film)|Grease]]'', ''[[Can't Stop the Music]]'', the musical adaptation of ''[[La Cage aux Folles (musical)|La Cage Aux Folles]]'', and the notorious [[61st Academy Awards|1989 Academy Awards]]. The film made its debut at the 2017 Seattle International Film Festival ([[SIFF]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siff.net/festival/fabulous-allan-carr-the|title=The Fabulous Allan Carr|website=www.siff.net}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestranger.com/movies/25117345/the-fabulous-allan-carr|title=The Fabulous Allan Carr (2017) - siff Guide - The Stranger|website=The Stranger}}</ref>\n\nFeaturing interviews and archival footage with friends and confidantes of the flamboyant producer, early reviews marked ''The Fabulous Allan Carr'' as a reverent portrait of one of Hollywood's elite,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scene-stealers.com/reviews/print-reviews/siff-2017-the-fabulous-allan-carr-movie-review/|title=\u2018The Fabulous Allan Carr\u2019 Movie Review|website=www.scene-stealers.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://thesunbreak.com/2017/05/19/siff-interview-jeffrey-schwarz-allan-carr/|title=SIFF Interview: Jeffrey Schwarz on Taking on \u2018The Fabulous Allan Carr\u2019|date=19 May 2017|publisher=}}</ref> highlighting the fact that Carr \"changed the face of pop and gay culture.\"\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://seattlegayscene.com/2017/05/siff-world-premiere-the-fabulous-allan-carr/|title=SIFF World Premiere: The Fabulous Allan Carr - Seattle Gay Scene - Your Daily Gay In Seattle|website=seattlegayscene.com}}</ref>\n\nThe film features interviews with [[Patricia Birch]], [[Maxwell Caulfield]], [[Steve Guttenberg]], [[Randy Jones (singer)|Randy Jones]], [[Randal Kleiser]], [[Sherry Lansing]], [[Lorna Luft]], [[Michael Musto]], [[Robert Osborne]], [[Brett Ratner]], [[Connie Stevens]], [[Alana Stewart]], [[Marlo Thomas]], [[Bruce Vilanch]] and more.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official|http://www.allancarrmovie.com/}}\n* {{facebook|allancarrmovie}}\n* {{imdb title|4704904}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fabulous Allan, The}}\n[[Category:Documentary films about film directors and producers]]\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American documentary films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n\n\n{{arts-documentary-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Fabulous_Allan_Carr"}
{"title_page": "Calamus (palm)", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n{{Automatic taxobox\n|image = Calamus gibbsianus.jpg\n|image_caption = ''[[Calamus gibbsianus]]''\n|display_parents = 2\n|taxon = Calamus (palm)\n|authority = [[Carl Linnaeus|L.]]\n|subdivision_ranks = Species\n|subdivision = Many, see text\n|synonyms_ref = <ref name=TPL/>\n|synonyms =\n*''Palmijuncus'' <small>Rumph. ex Kuntze</small> \n*''Rotanga'' <small>Boehm.</small>\n*''Rotang'' <small>Adans.</small>\n*''Zalaccella'' <small>[[Odoardo Beccari|Becc.]]</small>\n*''Calospatha'' <small>Becc.</small>\n*''Cornera'' <small>Furtado</small>\n*''Schizospatha'' <small>Furtado</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Calamus''''' is a [[genus]] of the palm family [[Arecaceae]]. These are among several genera known as [[rattan]] palms. There are an estimated 400 species in this genus, all native to tropical and subtropical [[Asia]], [[Africa]], and [[Australia]].<ref name=uiuiiiuiiiuiuiuiuiuiuiiii>{{cite web|url=http://apps.kew.org/wcsp/namedetail.do?name_id=29331|title=World Checklist of Selected Plant Families: Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew|author=|date=|website=apps.kew.org|accessdate=14 March 2018}}</ref><ref>Govaerts, R. & Dransfield, J. (2005). World Checklist of Palms: 1-223. The Board of Trustees of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew.</ref><ref>[http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=2&taxon_id=105020 Flora of China, Vol. 23 Page 135, <big>\u7701\u85e4\u5c5e</big> sheng teng sh, ''Calamus'' Linnaeus, Sp. Pl. 1: 325. 1753. ]</ref> They are mostly leaf-climbing [[liana]]s with slender, reedy stems. To aid scrambling some species have evolved hooks on the underside of the midrib, or more commonly by modified \"pinnae\" or [[tendril]]s in the form of stout, backward-pointing spines. These stems may grow to lengths of 200 metres.<ref>Dictionary of Flowering Plants and Ferns - JC Willis (1960)</ref>{{sfn|Dransfield|1978}}\n\n== Selected species ==\n\n[[The Plant List]] accepts 380 species,<ref name=TPL/> including:\n\n*''[[Calamus adspersus]]''\n*''[[Calamus aruensis]]'' <small>Becc.</small> \u2013 Bamaga wait-a-while<ref name=APNI/>\n*''[[Calamus australis]]''<small> Mart.</small> \u2013 lawyer cane, wait-a-while or hairy mary</small> <ref name=APNI/>  \n*''[[Calamus caryotoides]]'' <small>Mart.</small> \u2013 fishtail lawyer cane</small><ref name=APNI/>\n*''[[Calamus compsostachys]]''\n*''[[Calamus egregius]]''\n*''[[Calamus elegans]]'' <small>Becc. ex Ridl.</small>\n*''[[Calamus flagellum]]'' <small>Griff. ex Mart.</small>\n*''[[Calamus gibbsianus]]''   \n*''[[Calamus moti]]'' <small>F.M.Bailey</small><ref name=APNI/>\n*''[[Calamus manan]]'' <small>[[Miq.]]</small>\n*''[[Calamus manillensis]]'' \u2013 Philippines rattan or alimuran\n*''[[Calamus muelleri]]'' <small>H.Wendl.</small> \u2013 southern lawyer vine<ref name=APNI/>\n*''[[Calamus nambariensis]]''\n*''[[Calamus radicalis]]'' <small>H.Wendl. & Drude</small><ref name=APNI/>  \n*''[[Calamus rotang]]''\n*''[[Calamus suaveolens]]''<small> W.J.Baker & J. Dransf.</small><ref name=APNI/>\n*''[[Calamus tenuis]]''<ref>{{GRIN | ''Calamus tenuis'' | 8382 | accessdate = 2017-12-18}}</ref>\n*''[[Calamus viminalis]]'' <small> Willd.</small>\n*''[[Calamus vitiensis]]'' <small>Warb. ex Becc.</small> \u2013 Dunk Island lawyer vine, Mission Beach wait-a-while<ref name=APNI/>    \n*''[[Calamus wailong]]''\n*''[[Calamus warburgii]]'' <small>K.Schum.</small> \u2013 Iron Range wait-a-while<ref name=APNI>{{cite web |url=http://www.anbg.gov.au/cgi-bin/apni?TAXON_NAME=CALAMUS|title=''Calamus'' |accessdate=2008-03-28|work= [[Australian Plant Name Index]] (APNI), IBIS database|publisher = Centre for Plant Biodiversity Research, Australian Government, Canberra}}</ref>\n*''[[Calamus zeylanicus]]''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em|refs=\n<ref name=TPL>{{harvnb|TPL|2013|loc=[http://www.theplantlist.org/1.1/browse/A/Arecaceae/Calamus/ ''Calamus'']}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== Bibliography ==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite web|last1=TPL|authorlink=The Plant List |title=The Plant List Version 1.1|url=http://www.theplantlist.org/|publisher =[[Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew]] and [[Missouri Botanical Garden]] |accessdate=7 July 2015|date=2013|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|editor1-last=Tomlinson|editor1-first=P. B.|editor2-last=Zimmerman|editor2-first=Martin|title=Tropical Trees as Living Systems (Proceedings of the fourth Cabot Symposium held at Harvard Forest, Petersham Massachusetts on April 26-30, 1976)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oxT1M8-bu3IC|date=1978|publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]]|isbn=978-0-521-14247-2|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Dransfield|first1=John|authorlink=John Dransfield|title=Growth forms of rain forest palms|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oxT1M8-bu3IC&pg=PA247|pages=247\u2013268|ref={{harvid|Dransfield|1978}}}}, in {{harvtxt|Tomlinson|Zimmerman|1978}}{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Calamus (Arecaceae)}}\n{{WestAfricanPlants|Calamus deerratus}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q165260}}\n\n[[Category:Calamus (palm)| ]]\n[[Category:Arecaceae genera]]\n\n\n{{palm-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n{{Automatic taxobox\n|image = Calamus gibbsianus.jpg\n|image_caption = ''[[Calamus gibbsianus]]''\n|display_parents = 2\n|taxon = Calamus (palm)\n|authority = [[Carl Linnaeus|L.]]\n|subdivision_ranks = Species\n|subdivision = Many, see text\n|synonyms_ref = <ref name=TPL/>\n|synonyms =\n*''Palmijuncus'' <small>Rumph. ex Kuntze</small> \n*''Rotanga'' <small>Boehm.</small>\n*''Rotang'' <small>Adans.</small>\n*''Zalaccella'' <small>[[Odoardo Beccari|Becc.]]</small>\n*''Calospatha'' <small>Becc.</small>\n*''Cornera'' <small>Furtado</small>\n*''Schizospatha'' <small>Furtado</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Calamus''''' is a [[genus]] of the palm family [[Arecaceae]]. These are among several genera known as [[rattan]] palms. There are an estimated 400 species in this genus, all native to tropical and subtropical [[Asia]], [[Africa]], and [[Australia]].<ref name=uiuiiiuiiiuiuiuiuiuiuiiii>{{cite web|url=http://apps.kew.or