bsite=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Legal dispute===\nFollowing the announcement that ''Time to Hunt'' would be released on Netflix, Contents Panda filed an injunction against Little Big Pictures (distributor of the film) as they \"unilaterally notified [Contents Panda] of the termination of the contract\" and \"none of the overseas distributors agreed on an exclusive distribution agreement with Netflix.\"<ref>{{cite web|first=Gyu-lee|last=Lee|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/04/398_287567.html|title=Film 'Time to Hunt' faces lawsuit over Netflix debut|date=April 8, 2020|website=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs of April 8, 2020 Netflix announced the release date has been postponed to comply with the Seoul Central District Court ruling regarding distribution contracts, and no further info for a posible release date was given.<ref>{{cite web|first=Gyu-lee|last=Lee|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/04/689_287636.html|title=Netflix halts 'Time to Hunt' release, promotion after injunction|date=April 9, 2020|website=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nOn the review aggregation website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 83% based on 6 reviews, with an average rating of 8/10.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/time_to_hunt|title=Time to Hunt (2020)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=March 25, 2020}}</ref>\n\nDeborah Young of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' describes it as \"a technical tour-de-force running over two hours [which] belongs both to the East Asian testosterone-powered action genre whose unrelenting tension will be reward in itself for fans, as well as to socially conscious coming-of-age stories whose painstaking character development adds a deeper sense of realism.\"<ref>{{cite web|first=Deborah|last=Young|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/time-hunt-review-1280622|title='Time to Hunt' ('Sa-nyang-eui-si-gan'): Film Review / Berlin 2020|date=February 22, 2020|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|11777040}}\n\n[[Category:2020 films]] \n[[Category:Korean-language films]]\n[[Category:South Korean films]]\n[[Category:South Korean crime thriller films]]\n[[Category:Netflix original films]]\n[[Category:Films postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Films not released in theaters due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "name_user": "Seokgjin", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_to_Hunt_(film)"}
